images.caption: Figure 2:Overview ofUnmasking with Contrastive Attention Guidance (UNCAGE). Without UNCAGE, as shown att=3t=3, the model fails to select (unmask) the apple-related token despite generating a reasonable candidate, resulting in an image that contains only the car. In contrast, with UNCAGE, it effectively identifies tokens that clearly represent each object, allowing the model to select the apple-related token att=3t=3and successfully generate both the car and the apple in the final image.
